line
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:a formed road, often extant in modern street or road names
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1960 There are `lines' (i.e. `roads') in many districts e.g. White's Line (Hutt Valley) and very frequent in the Manawatu.
